  "text": "Hoffman et al. (2012) did research on 290 women with breast cancer after surgery, chemotherapy, and radiotherapy. They showed that eight sessions of cognitive therapy based on stress reduction in subjects can improve the quality of life depending on endocrine in women with breast cancer at stage 0 to 3 [CITATION_1] .",
